.TH "batadv_bla_answer_request" 9 "batadv_bla_answer_request" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
batadv_bla_answer_request \- answer a bla request by sending own claims
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" batadv_bla_answer_request
.BI "(struct batadv_priv *bat_priv "  ","
.BI "struct batadv_hard_iface *primary_if "  ","
.BI "unsigned short vid "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bat_priv" 12
the bat priv with all the soft interface information
.IP "primary_if" 12
interface where the request came on
.IP "vid" 12
the vid where the request came on
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Repeat all of our own claims, and finally send an ANNOUNCE frame
to allow the requester another check if the CRC is correct now.
